        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Polish Workboard operations view",
        "body": "## Summary\n- polish the Workboard operations UI across card layout, filters, health metrics, details, responsive behavior, dropdowns, and tooltips\n- add guarded auto-refresh, serialized writes, linked-task reconciliation, bounded task discovery, and safer start/stop behavior\n- preserve accessible names, selected custom-select values, tooltip viewport behavior, and native-title fallback semantics\n- expand focused controller/view/tooltip/lifecycle coverage and deterministic Workboard browser E2E\n\n## Maintenance repairs\n- rebased onto current Workboard base behavior while preserving main's hide-empty-column and accessibility changes\n- deferred failed lifecycle refresh retries, preserved matching task links on enrichment failure, and committed poll results atomically so in-flight polls cannot disrupt drag-and-drop\n- hardened canonical/replacement task matching, terminal discovery cursor cycling, unresolved-start tracking, and task/session stop fallback behavior\n- removed an unreachable same-card details toggle while keeping the modal/inert interaction model intact\n- hardened shared floating tooltip cleanup, viewport placement, accessible descriptions, and inherited native-title suppression\n- made custom-select triggers announce both their field and selected value\n\n## Verification\nProof was run on exact pushed head `8d8b4680a8611887f84a2a6d0c82e291cf687d1e`.\n\n- `git merge-tree --write-tree HEAD upstream/main` - clean against current `upstream/main` `c9c19a1106699bb633b74dd67b89cb771cf4069e`\n- `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD`\n- focused UI suite - 7 files, 261 tests passed\n- complete UI shard - 113 files, 1,525 tests passed\n- Workboard browser E2E - 2 files, 2 tests passed\n- `pnpm tsgo:test:ui`\n- `pnpm ui:i18n:check`\n- scoped `oxfmt --check` and `oxlint` for changed Workboard and tooltip surfaces\n- trusted host-broker `kepler-alpha` high autoreview - clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: Workboard operations layout and flows; serialized writes; guarded refresh, polling, drag-and-drop, disconnect, and linked-task reconciliation; bounded paginated discovery; exact-confirmed missing-task handling; replacement-task polling/stopping; unresolved-run start suppression; custom-select keyboard/value accessibility; and shared tooltip lifecycle/viewport behavior.\n\nReal environment tested: local OpenClaw PR branch at exact pushed head `8d8b4680a8611887f84a2a6d0c82e291cf687d1e`, using the real local Workboard plugin state plus deterministic Control UI browser E2E. No live operator channel, protected channel, configured binding, or test fixture was mutated.\n\nExact-head read-only CLI evidence:\n```text\n$ pnpm openclaw --version\nOpenClaw 2026.6.2 (8d8b468)\n\n$ pnpm openclaw plugins list --enabled --json | <redacted summary>\n{\n  \"enabledCount\": 80,\n  \"workboard\": {\n    \"id\": \"workboard\",\n    \"enabled\": true\n  }\n}\n\n$ pnpm openclaw workboard list --json | <redacted summary>\n{\n  \"cardCount\": 10,\n  \"statuses\": {\n    \"triage\": 1,\n    \"backlog\": 1,\n    \"todo\": 1,\n    \"scheduled\": 1,\n    \"ready\": 3,\n    \"review\": 1,\n    \"blocked\": 1,\n    \"done\": 1\n  },\n  \"readyByAgent\": {\n    \"main\": 2,\n    \"gadget\": 1\n  }\n}\n```\n\nExisting visual references for the unchanged tooltip geometry:\n- bottom-edge tooltip: https://files.catbox.moe/dkiz3z.png\n- topbar tooltip: https://files.catbox.moe/oh0dhw.png\n- tooltip recording: https://files.catbox.moe/zfe01o.webm\n\nObserved result after fix: the live Workboard plugin remains enabled and its read-only CLI lists the expected 10-card status summary. Exact-head tests and browser E2E cover guarded refresh, drag-safe atomic polls, paginated discovery cycling, failed-enrichment link preservation, unresolved-run starts, strict stop fallback, custom-select accessibility, and tooltip title/viewport behavior. Final trusted broker autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings.\n\nWhat was not tested: no production Gateway or private card contents were dumped. The local CLI emitted pre-existing config-version and plugin-index migration warnings; they did not block Workboard plugin discovery or card listing. No live channel mutation, QA fixture, Crabbox, Testbox, or Mantis run was needed. Routine CI is running with no failures observed at closeout.",
